Manchester United’s EFL Cup (Carabao Cup) final squad to face Newcastle United has been revealed. According to MEN, Man United boss Erik ten Hag has released a list of 22 players to tackle Newcastle United in the EFL Cup on Sunday evening at Wembley Stadium. The Red Devils head to the game following a 2-1 victory over Barcelona in the UEFA Europa League last Thursday. Here is Man United’s squad against Newcastle: De Gea, Heaton, Butland, Dalot, Wan-Bissaka, Varane, Martinez, Lindelof, Maguire, Shaw, Malacia, Casemiro, McTominay, Fred, Sabitzer, Elanga, Fernandes, Sancho, Garnacho, Antony, Rashford, Weghorst The kick-off time for the match is 5.30 pm.